solution.p:
        In the right triangle, the horizontal leg has length \sqrt{1-x^2} by the Pythagorean Theorem.



\sin(\theta) = x


\sec(\theta) = \dfrac{1}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}


\csc(\theta) = \dfrac{1}{x}


\tan(\theta) = \dfrac{x}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}


\cos(\arcsin(x)) = \cos(\theta) = \sqrt{1-x^2}


\cot(\arcsin(x)) = \cot(\theta) = \dfrac{\sqrt{1-x^2}}{x}
